law.text:
A member who is subject to this part shall:
receive an allowance for all creditable service as follows:
for normal service retirement as provided in § 23-401(d) of this title;
for early service retirement as provided in § 23-402 of this title;
for ordinary disability retirement as provided in § 29-108 of this article; and
for accidental disability retirement as provided in § 29-110 of this article;
have the allowance adjusted as provided in Title 29, Subtitle 4 of this article; and
make the member contributions at the rate specified in § 23-212(c) of this subtitle.
